mplications, but as a transitional and transgressional text that has challenged law and heteronormativity.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aJudgeszGermanyy19th centuryvBiography. 0aJurisprudencezGermany. 0aLawzGermany. 7aLAW / General.2bisacsh  aJudge Schreber.  aclinic and critique.  alaw and gender.  alaw and psychoanalysis.  apsychotheology.  aqueer legal theory.  atransgender.1 aGandorfer, Daniela, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGephart, Werner, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGherovici, Patricia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGoodrich, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGoodrich, Peter, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMitchell, W.J.T., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSaikumar, Rajgopal, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSanders, Mark, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchmitz, Ludwig, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTarizzo, Davide, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTrüstedt, Katrin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTrüstedt, Katrin, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311076715540uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978148753981840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781487539818423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781487539818/original  a978-3-11-076715-5  University of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  aGBV-deGruyter-alles